===Etymology===
First attested in 1624; from the {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|πολυμαθής||having learnt much}}, from {{m|grc|πολύς||much}} + {{m|grc|μάθη}} (''mathē'', “learning”; from {{m|grc|μανθάνω}}, ''manthanō'' “I learn”); compare {{m|en|opsimath}}, {{m|en|philomath}}, {{m|en|polyhistor}}, {{m|en|polymathic}}, {{m|en|polymathist}}, and {{m|en|polymathy}}, as well as the {{cog|fr|polymathe}}.

